I felt the service could have been better and more attentive for a new restaurant. The interior decor was very nice.
Amazing food. Delivery came quick.
Great family spot. . kid friendly and fun and can't beat the food.. It is delicious!! worth the price!

4 stars on deco- The ambience of the restaurant was absolutely beautiful and the decorations were outstanding. 2 stars on food and wait time. The food was pretty good just disappointing that you have to pay for rice separately which I’ve never experienced in any hibachi place. Everything was cooked well but one of my issue was the wait time for service just to get our order placed. There was another set of family that were waiting for other members so we couldn’t order even though my family was ready. Then once we were all seated we find that there were only two chefs and the place was full. I saw two sets of family leave because they didn’t want to wait any longer. Then the family next to us get there and were just to busy getting up and out of there seats to make phone calls so when our waiter came to the table he has to come back again until the other person remain seated to take everyone’s order. Now, My wife and I (female) we are a lesbian couple with two boys...My next issue was even though it was all for entertainment the cook jokes with a gentleman about his girlfriend and the man stated he was gay joking back. That is where the cook looks over to my 12 year old son and Refers him to kiss a child to prove he was gay. which I found absolutely disgusting and was I completely on guard to defend my child and felt that was inappropriate of him to say that. Joke with the adults and make all the gay comments you want I don’t care but when it comes to children let’s not involve them. Also, I’m not one to have any allergic reaction to any food. However after ordering what I normally order at every hibachi place 10 minutes after I left the restaurant I ended up at the urgent care with a serious allergic reaction to whatever seasoning was used. Having to have a oxygen tank just to breathe and two shots for all the tracks on my body. NEVER GOING BACK!
Great place and staff are very friendly !!! Love the Decor !!! Food was very delish and nice size portions ! Drinks were good !!! Will be going back very soon for the hibachi !!!

Food was delicious but most importantly FRESH and nothing was overcooked. The portions were just right, but I did find it weird that the rice was a separate line item on the bill. The place is decorated tastefully. Great job and best of luck to them. Oh! And don't forget to make a wish as you tip the budda on your way out!
I went to Ikko last week. I had a lovely experience. The ambiance was fantastic, the food was fresh and very tasty. I felt as if I was transported to Japan. I can’t wait to go back!

The food was great. The decor was beautiful the vibe is nice , can get a little loud in the Hibachi section and if you come on a weekend at night with a wait of people you have to share the hibachi tables with other guest  which can be a little awkward sitting next to random strangers especially if your with your kids making messes and can’t manage to stay still. I did not like the fact you had to pay for the fried rice separately after the meal is already priced. Over all I enjoyed my dinner and left a clean plate . The kids getting balloons was a bonus

Going with five stars even though there’s room for improvement. Place is absolutely gorgeous. Modern Japanese decor. Food was great. Cook was entertaining and well skilled in hibachi preparation. Wait service could be better. Drinks were great, but no ice cream included with meal. Everyone in Bronx Westchester area expects that treat as their competition always included. Hope the tweak their policy cause it’s a great addition to Throggs Neck dining options.  Enjoy!
Special decoration style! Perfect with food! Plus warm service! Bring you a different feeling! They should be worth promoting in New York!

Went to eat here today. They just opened a few days ago. Decor is top of the line but the reason for my 1 star is the amount of food you get and to top it off you don’t get rice with your hibachi dinner. You actually have to order it separately and pay extra. I’ve been to many hibachi restaurants and this is a first. I always look forward to the rice and we were jerked.  I find it to be expensive and not have rice included. We left there hungry. Need i say more.
